/opt/drbl/sbin/dcs: --help: invalid option

Usage: /opt/drbl/sbin/dcs [OPTION] MODE [MODE2]

OPTION

-l, --language INDEX Set the language to be shown by index number:
       [0|en_US.UTF-8]: English,
       [1|zh_TW.BIG5]: Traditional Chinese (Big5) - Taiwan,
       [2|zh_TW.UTF-8]: Traditional Chinese (UTF-8, Unicode) - Taiwan
       [a|ask]: Prompt to ask the language index
-h, --host [IP_LIST|MAC_LIST] Instead of all DRBL clients, assign some DRBL clients (IP_LIST or MAC_LIST) to be processed, if IP_LIST or MAC_LIST is not set, a dialog menu will be shown so that the target DRBL client(s) can be selected. The IP_LIST is like: "192.168.0.1 192.168.0.2", and the MAC_LIST is like "00:50:56:01:02:01 00:50:56:01:02:02". NOTE!!! You must put " " before and after the IP_LIST or MAC_LIST!
-nl, --no-list-host   Set all clients' mode (This is default)
 -d0, --dialog         Use dialog
 -d1, --Xdialog        Use Xdialog
 -d2, --whiptail       Use whiptail
 -d3, --gdialog        Use gdialog
 -d4, --kdialog        Use kdialog

MODE:

remote-linux-gra      Client machine will boot from DRBL server,
                      and enter graphic mode, for powerful client.
remote-linux-txt      Client machine will boot from DRBL server,
                      and enter text mode, for powerful client.
terminal              Remote display Linux, terminal mode.
remote-memtest        Remote boot to run memtest86
remote-fdos           Remote boot to run FreeDOS
clonezilla-start      Start Clonezilla mode
clonezilla-stop       Stop the clonezilla mode
local                 Client machine will boot from local (now PXE only)
reboot                Reboot DRBL clients now
shutdown              Shutdown DRBL clients now
Wake-on-LAN           Turn on DRBL clients by Wake-on-LAN now
netinstall            Let clients to install Linux distribution via network (PXE/etherboot)

MODE2:

Based on MODE, assign the 2nd level mode:

For MODE=clonezilla-start, available MODE2:

save-disk: Clonezilla save disk mode
restore-disk: Clonezilla restore disk Mode
save-parts: Clonezilla save partitions mode
restore-parts: Clonezilla restore partitions mode

For MODE=more, available MODE2:

switch-pxe-menu       Switch DRBL client menus
switch-pxe-bg-mode    Switch PXE Linux background
drbl-mode             Switch diskless linux mode
clonezilla-mode       Switch clonezilla mode
login-switch          Switch DRBL client login mode
switch-drbl-serv      Start, stop or restart DRBL related services in DRBL server
client-reautologin    Force to restart client autologin
clean-autologin-account Delete all autologin accounts
re-deploy             Re-deploy files to clients, i.e. update the files of server to clients.
clean-dhcpd-lease     Force to reset DHCP IP address leases

If no argument is specified, a dialog will appear to let you choose the mode!

EXAMPLE

  To turn off the local and memtest boot menues of clients, run:
  /opt/drbl/sbin/dcs -nl more switch-pxe-menu '-i local -i memtest hide'
  To switch client's PXE boot menu as graphic mode, run:
  /opt/drbl/sbin/dcs -nl more switch-pxe-bg-mode graphic
  To restart drbl-related service, run:
  /opt/drbl/sbin/dcs -nl more switch-drbl-serv restart

